    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "nitrogen deficiency makes sense. i think i might have used some old compost. how do i figure out if the soil ph is actually the problem preventing them from taking up the nitrogen? do i need to buy a specific kit for that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A soil pH issue is a real possibility, and you're right to suspect it! It's much more precise than just guessing, and you don't need to just throw in random amendments. You absolutely need a soil test kit, which can be a simple home kit or you can send a sample to a local agricultural extension office for a professional reading. These kits will tell you exactly what your soil is doing, which is crucial because if the pH is too high or too low, even if the nitrogen is there, the plants can't absorb it.",
      "source": "target",
